column169: On February 3, 2025, one (1) 330-gallon tote of phosphoric acid was punctured and released approximately 330-gallons of product to the asphalt pavement and nearby storm drain. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from Thin Line Environmental (TLE) to remediate the impacted site. TLE personnel noted that the product released into a storm drain onsite and began utilizing a vacuum trailer to remove the liquids at each storm drain between the terminal building and the retention pond. All acid impacted liquids were collected and containerized into three (3) 330-gallon totes and one (1) 275-gallon tote and staged onsite for further management.

column169: AT THE KARLSRUHE CENTER IN GERMANY ONE FULLY DECLARED DANGEROUS GOODS PACKAGE ARRIVED WITH EVIDENCE OF HAVNG UNDERGONE A PREVIOUS LITHIUM BATTERY THERMAL EVENT. THE OUTER BOX HAS SEVERAL VISIBLE PUNCTURE HOLES WITH EVIDENCE OF CHARRING. AT THE TIME OF DISCOVERY THE PACKAGE WAS NOT WARM AND WAS NOT IN AN ACTIVE THERMAL EVENT.  UPON CONTENT INSPECTION, TWO LITHIUM ION BATTERIES HAVE A BURN APPEARANCE ON THEIR METAL POLES WITH SLIGHT CHARRING AROUND THE POLES. THE LITHIUM-ION BATTERY POLES HAVE PUNCTURED THROUGH TO THE OUTER BOX. THE OUTER BOX IS UN SPECIFICAITON PACKAGING 4G/Y30/S/24/SGP/SCL 033. THE OUTER BOX HAS APPROPRIATE DANGEROUS GOODS MARKS AND LABELS WITH A DANGEROUS GOODS UPS ACCEPTED STICKER HAVING PREVIOUSLY PASSED AN ACCEPTANCE AUDIT AT THE ORIGIN FACILITY IN HONG KONG. A TELEPHONE REPORT WAS VERBALLY MADE TO THE NATIONAL RESPONSE CENTER AS REQUIRED PER 171.15 ON 05-FEBRUARY-2025 UNDER NRC 1422799.

column169: AT THE UPS FACILITY IN COLOGNE, GERMANY, ONE AIR PACKAGE FROM USA TO GERMANY WAS FOUND SOILED WITH A VERY STRONG ODOR. THE PACKAGE HAS AN EXCEPTED QUANTITY MARK APPLIED TO THE PACKAGE WITH CLASSES INDICATED AS 3, 4.1, 6.1, 8, AND 9.  CONTENT INSPECTION REVEALS MULTIPLE GLASS BOTTLES INSIDE WITH SEVERAL SHATTERED AND LEAKING. SEVEN GLASS BOTTLES ARE 500 ML SIZE EACH. SIXTEEN GLASS BOTTLES ARE 30 ML EACH. THE REGULATED CONTENTS INSIDE THE BOX ARE EXCEPTED QUANTITIES OF MATERIALS CLASSIFIED AS UN2874, FURFURYL ALCOHOL, 6.1, PG III, UN3265 CORROSIVE LIQUID ACIDIC ORGANOS NOS, CLASS 8, PG III, UN1224 KETONES LIQUID NOS, CLASS 3, PG III, UN1325 FLAMMABLE SOLIDS ORGANIC NOS, CLASS 4.1, PG III, AND UN1197 EXTRACTS FLAVORING LIQUID, CLASS 3, PG II.  THERE ARE ADDITIONAL CHEMICALS INSIDE THE BOX THAT ARE NOT REGULATED IN TRANSPORTATION. THE PACKAGE AND CONTENTS WILL BE DISPOSED OF.

column169: On February 7, 2025, one (1) 55-gallon drum of printing ink was punctured and released approximately one (1) gallon of product to the dock floor. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from Republic Services (RS) to remediate the site. The crew utilized absorbents and hand tools to remediate the site. RS personnel dismantled the impacted pallet as well. All waste was containerized in one (1) 55-gallon drum. The damaged drum was containerized in one (1) 85-gallon drum.

column169: On February 6, 2025, one (1) 55-gallon drum of paint released approximately ten (10) gallons of product to the trailer interior and pavement beneath. R+L Carriers retained Cura Emergency Services, LC who dispatched a crew from Indiana Spill Response (ISR) to remediate the site. The crew utilized absorbents and hand tools to remediate the sites and containerized all impacted materials in two (2) 55-gallon drums. The damaged drum of product was overpacked in one (1) 85-gallon drum.
